CSSPAfterAttribute

Custom validation attribute used when creating code

Used when creating [class]ServiceGenerated.cs and [class]ServiceTestGenerated.cs codes

Used on type: System.DateTime

DateTime only valid for years after Year

Year: Determine the year for which the DateTime has to be after

CSSPAllowNullAttribute

Custom validation attribute used when creating code

Used when creating [class]ServiceGenerated.cs and [class]ServiceTestGenerated.cs codes

Used on type: System.String

Used when creating validation and testing on string properties when nullable

No parameter

CSSPBiggerAttribute

Custom validation attribute used when creating code

Used when creating [class]ServiceGenerated.cs and [class]ServiceTestGenerated.cs codes

Used on type: System.DateTime

DateTime only valid if DateTime of OtherField is smaller or equal

OtherField: Determine the other field for which the DateTime has to be bigger

CSSPEnumTypeAttribute

Custom validation attribute used when creating code

Used when creating [class]ServiceGenerated.cs and [class]ServiceTestGenerated.cs codes

Used on type: Enumeration properties

Only valid if the Enum value is one of existing Enum

No parameter

CSSPEnumTypeTextAttribute

Custom validation attribute used when creating code

Used when creating [class]ServiceGenerated.cs and [class]ServiceTestGenerated.cs codes

Used on type: Enumeration properties

Used when creating Fill of services for enumeration

EnumTypeName: Enumeration name within CSSPEnums

EnumType: Property name

CSSPExistAttribute

Custom validation attribute used when creating code

Used when creating [class]ServiceGenerated.cs and [class]ServiceTestGenerated.cs codes

Used on type: int which represend the ID of database field key

ExistTypeName: Object Type text representing the name of the type

ExistPlurial: Plurial of the type which together creates the table name of the DB

ExistFieldID: Field ID of the table for which to compare with

AllowableTVTypeList: List of TVTypeEnum numbers separated by commas (only used with TVItems DB table)

CSSPFillAttribute

Custom validation attribute used when creating code

Used when creating [class]ServiceGenerated.cs and [class]ServiceTestGenerated.cs codes

Used on various types

FillTypeName: Object Type text representing the name of the type

FillPlurial: Plurial of the type which together creates the table name of the DB

FillFieldID: Field ID of the table for which to compare with

FillEqualField: Field name/value to compare with DB table

FillReturnField: Field name/value to return

FillNeedLanguage: If true, a language comparision will also be included
